Maziar Rezaei,Matthew Gramolini,2014-08-05T17:04:17.157Z,43209,1354,"Constellation.Html contains two useful features:

column3: 1. Extension methods for HtmlTextWriter. - Internally these methods use an IDisposable pattern to encapsulate the rather cumbersome code for adding attributes, rendering the begin tag, and rendering the end tag.
The extension methods should generally be called as part of a ""using"" statement. ex: using (writer.RenderDiv()) { }
2. A dynamic wrapper for HtmlTextWriter that allows for very expressive and flexible HTML output writing within C#

The result is C# code for rendering HTML that is very easy to read, fully supports the ASP.NET browser capabilities feature, and is flexible enough to handle new tags invented in the future.",Constellation.Html,False,1900-01-01T00:00:00+00:00,False,False,A .NET library to increase the utility and efficiency of HtmlTextWriter,Sitecore,2471,False,1.7.5330.21682

Richard J. Cabral,2015-07-24T20:01:57.09Z,43209,1001,"This library introduces ease of use for handmade ViewModels that represent IPublishedContent items. The ViewModels should inherit from Models.ContetnViewModel in order to take advantage of the

column3: automatic property mapping provided by this library.
To Use:

column4: 1. Create ViewModels that represent content. ViewModel properties should match types and names of the published content Properties[] collection.
2. Each ViewModel should have a ContentType attribute on the class that specifies the Alias for the content that it represents.
3. To convert a PublishedContent to a ViewModel, use the extension methods provided in this library. You may automatically cast to the ""best fit"" type, or you may cast to a specific ViewModel type.

column3: This library was ported from concepts in Constellation.Sitecore.Items - it is not a 1:1 match, expect evolution.",Constellation.Umbraco,False,1900-01-01T00:00:00+00:00,False,False,A library for Controller-based Umbraco installations.,Umbraco,1043,False,1.0.5683.27032

column1: Ed Lane,Matt Schroer,2016-01-26T15:29:56.097Z,43209,815,"This library supports a number of regularly-requested SEO features, implemented in Sitecore. Some of these have been implemented elsewhere, this approach

column3: is stronger for multi-site, multi-language installations.
Features Included:
Browser-based language detection and setting of the context language with the ability to generalize from a specific dialect to a fallback master
for a given language (ex: fr-CA will fall back to fr)
Multi-site 404 page subsystem that returns an actual 404 response code.
Automatic Robots.txt support - configurable for each Sitecore server in your installation.
Automatic Sitemap.xml support - fully multi-site capable; can be configured to support a wide array of information architectures.
Rule-based approach to ensuring that Sitecore Items get the most url-friendly name possible.

Site definition extension allowing for dynamic, site-based hostname resolution for static assets such as javsacript and CSS files.",Constellation.Sitecore.Seo,False,1900-01-01T00:00:00+00:00,False,False,A number of SEO-specific modules for Sitecore.,Sitecore,7515,False,3.0.5869.18858
